-- Euro Weakens for a Third Day Against Dollar Amid Greece Debt-Swap Talks
-- B y   M a s a k i   K o n d o
-- 2012-02-01T06:35:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/euro-weakens-for-a-third-day-against-dollar-amid-greece-debt-swap-talks.html
The euro weakened for a third day as
 Greece  struggles to conclude debt-swap talks with creditors by
the end of this week.  The 17-nation currency slid 0.3 percent to $1.3050 as of
6:34 a.m. in  London . The euro lost 0.3 percent to 99.48 yen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
